Class CanovaSequencePairDataSetFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.deeplearning4j.spark.canova.CanovaSequencePairDataSetFunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.apache.spark.api.java.function.Function<scala.Tuple2<java.util.Collection<java.util.Collection<Writable>>,java.util.Collection<java.util.Collection<Writable>>>,DataSet>

    public class CanovaSequencePairDataSetFunction
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.spark.api.java.function.Function<scala.Tuple2<java.util.Collection<java.util.Collection<Writable>>,java.util.Collection<java.util.Collection<Writable>>>,DataSet>, java.io.Serializable
    Map Tuple2<Collection<Collection<Writable>>,Collection<Collection<Writable>> objects (out of a TWO canova-spark sequence record reader functions) to DataSet objects for Spark training. Analogous to SequenceRecordReaderDataSetIterator, but in the context of Spark. Supports loading data from a TWO sources only; hence supports many-to-one and one-to-many situations. see CanovaSequenceDataSetFunction for the single file version
